  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Satellites for Sustainable fishing-Inmarsat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Currently the estimated loss of revenue attributed to illegal fishing is $20bn. Using Inmarsat satellite communication satellites to monitor vessel tracking, this project will allow the design of new operational protocols for policing and fisheries management in Indonesia and will incentivise fishermen to use Vessel Monitoring Systems (VMS) actively. It will also strengthen the surveillance capabilities of the Ministry of Fishing, improving the policing of illegal fishing as well as providing valuable industry information on catches and sourcing.</narrative>
  </description>
